main event: Thirteen unidentified objects were observed decelerating and falling into the water near Patrick AFB, Florida.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on January 26, 1959, at 2245Z., The objects were evaluated as missile debris within two hours after the initial report., A civilian source reported the sighting., The objects were reported to be falling in a specific location (27-52N 79-44W)., An investigation request was noted from the U.S. Air Force regarding the incident.
location: 50 MI SE of Patrick AFB, Florida, USA
